    },
	{
      "text": "Reference your application on the subject noted above",
	  "margin": [
        0,
        10,
        0,
        0
      ]
    },
	{
      "text": "Consequent upon the approval of the Chief Administrator-cum-Commissioner, Municipal Corporation, Chandigarh, permission is hereby granted permission to display branding/advertisements at the venue i.e. {{variable6}} on {{variable7}} to {{variable8}}. The payment of Rs. {{variable9}} as the ground rent/ advertisement fees have been received on {{variable10}} under Chandigarh Advertisement Control Order, 1954 with subject to the following terms & conditions: -",
	  "margin": [
        0,
        10,
        0,
        0
      ]
    },
	{
      "text": "   1. No advertisement or sky -sign shall be put up as is considered by the Chief Administrator to offend against good taste, decency and public morals.",
	  "margin": [
        0,
        15,
        0,
        0
      ]
    },
	{
      "text": "   2. All advertisement displayed and any land used for the display of advertisement shall be maintained in a clean and tidy condition to the satisfaction of the Chief Administrator",
	  "margin": [
        0,
        5,
        0,
        0
      ]
    },
	{
      "text": "   3. No advertisement shall be sited or displayed to obstruct the vision of drivers of vehicular traffic or to hinder the ready interpretation of any road traffic sign, railway or air signal.",
	  "margin": [
        0,
        5,
        0,
        0
      ]
    },
	{
      "text": "   4. Permission will be valid for display of banner of the above mentioned size at designated placed only.",
	  "margin": [
        0,
        5,
        0,
        0
      ]
    },
	{
      "text": "   5. Banner/Advertisement should be removed immediate after the completion of permission period.",
	  "margin": [
        0,
        5,
        0,
        0
      ]
    },
	{
      "text": "   6. No inconvenience should be caused to the General Public on account of the permission.",
	  "margin": [
        0,
        5,
        0,
        0
      ]
    },
	{
      "text": "   7. The Chief Administrator cum Commissioner, Municipal Corporation, Chandigarh reserves the right to cancel the booking without assigning reason in public interest.",
	  "margin": [
        0,
        5,
        0,
        0
      ]
    },
	{
      "text": "   8. If the Banners/Hoardings/Advertisement shall not remove within the period mention in the letter then you will  be liable to pay a sum equal to 25% of the fees due as a penalty, in addition to any other action as per rule.",
	  "margin": [
        0,
        5,
        0,
        0
      ]
    },
	{
      "text": "   9. The Chief Administrator shall not be liable to any damage caused to any property through the fall of any advertisement board or any appurtenance or fixture thereof.",
	  "margin": [
        0,
        5,
        0,
        0
      ]
